# Endpoint Delivery Artifacts Rules

## Purpose
Ensure every new endpoint ships with executable API artifacts and regression protection.

## Trigger
- A feature introduces a new endpoint (new method + path), or a new externally used endpoint variant.

## Mandatory Artifacts
- Add a Bruno request for the endpoint under `bruno/golang-clean/<Module>/`.
- Include required headers, request body (if any), and expected success shape in Bruno request.
- Add integration test coverage in Bruno (as runnable request/scenario) for:
  - happy path
  - at least one failure/validation case

## Contract Change Rule
- If endpoint contract changes (request fields, response shape, status code, error contract), update related Bruno files and Bruno integration scenarios in the same change set.

## Completion Rule
- Do not mark the task done without Bruno request + Bruno integration scenario updates for new endpoints.
- If environment blockers prevent Bruno integration execution, report blocker explicitly and request user decision before closing the task.
